  "body": "After installing hardhat with:\r\n`$ npm install --save-dev hardhat`\r\n\r\nAnd attempting to start hardhat with:\r\n`$ npx hardhat node`\r\n\r\nHardhat does not present the \"What do you want to do?\" prompt with options to create a sample project or empty config file. It simply presents:\r\n```\r\nError HH1: You are not inside a Hardhat project.\r\n\r\nFor more info go to https://hardhat.org/HH1 or run Hardhat with --show-stack-traces\r\n```\r\n\r\nTested on:\r\n- OS: Windows 10 Pro\r\n- Hardhat: v2.0.11\r\n- Node: v14.11.0, v14.16.0, v10.24.0\r\n- NPM: 6.14.4\r\n\r\nIt however worked as intended on newly created Ubuntu VM:\r\n- OS: Ubuntu 20.04 LTS\r\n- Hardhat: v2.0.11\r\n- Node: v10.19.0\r\n- NPM: 6.14.4",
